replies.body:
You don't seem to understand. You didn't get banned by some Riot employee sitting there reading your chatlog. You got banned by the instant feedback system, which automatically reads your chat logs if you get reported.
You got banned because this system has a zero tolerance policy, meaning: it encounters certain words, it bans or punishes you. Without checking context.  So no, what I wrote is not incorrect, it is actually very correct. I never said you cannot appeal. I never said they wouldn't revert it if appropriate. Hell, they unbanned Tyler1, that should set an example. I said: Don't EFFING write those words at all, EVER, and you won't EVER be in that situation. Is that so hard to do, refraining from saying those words?

Please research before you spread fake news on the board. thanks.{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}

Well, that just shows you ran out of arguments and are trying to save face without having to admit it.
I'll take it though, a win is a win.
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
